abstract_ssm: The Herman Mark Collection documents the personal and profession life of Herman Francis Mark, the Father of Polymer Science.  During his fifty years at the Polytechnic Institute of Brooklyn, Mark developed the field of polymer science in the United States, published over 600 articles, and founded the Institute of Polymer Research, the first graduate program of its kind in America.
